From: Jeff Mahoney <jeffm@suse.com>
Subject: hv_mouse: needs <linux/delay.h>
Patch-mainline: Submitted 12 Apr 2011

 The hv_mouse dirver uses udelay() but doesn't include <linux/delay.h>. This
 causes build failures (at least) on x86_64.

Signed-off-by: Jeff Mahoney <jeffm@suse.com>
---

 drivers/staging/hv/hv_mouse.c |    1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

--- a/drivers/staging/hv/hv_mouse.c
+++ b/drivers/staging/hv/hv_mouse.c
@@ -23,6 +23,7 @@
 #include <linux/hiddev.h>
 #include <linux/pci.h>
 #include <linux/dmi.h>
+#include <linux/delay.h>
 
 #include "hv_api.h"
 #include "logging.h"
